The article discusses the appointment of two senior officials responsible for Iraqi refugees and internally displaced persons. President Obama has committed to working closely with the Iraqi government to aid those who have been displaced or are vulnerable due to the violence in Iraq. Samantha Power, Senior Director for Multilateral Affairs and Human Rights at the National Security Council, will coordinate the efforts of various US government departments on this issue. Mark Storella, a Senior Foreign Service officer, has also been appointed to coordinate the government's work in Iraq on refugees and internally displaced persons. He will represent the United States in its dealings with the Iraqi government, the international community, and non-governmental organizations.